cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about image denoising using a fully-convolutional network model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of identity mappings and dilated kernels, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and machine learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional layers and neural networks suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category. Finally, the paper focuses on image processing, which is a subfield of multimedia, suggesting that cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category.
